      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut your<strong> cucumber</strong> in half lengthways, then slice finely</p><p>Wash your<strong> salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Combine the <strong>remaining Dijon mustard</strong> with your <strong>honey</strong>, <strong>cider vinegar</strong>, a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>pepper </strong>in a large bowl – this is your<strong> dressing</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> salad </strong>and<strong> sliced cucumber </strong>to the dressing and toss – this is your <strong>bistro salad</strong></p>",
